properties.Name: TransCanada - Keystone XL (3)
properties.Image: In 20ll, scientist James Hansen declared it would be game over for a viable climate if Canada's Tar Sands were fully exploited. In 2015, President Obama yielded to the pressure of millions of grassroots activists and rejected the Keystone XL pipeline.

properties.Name: Enbridge - Northern Gateway
properties.Image: On June 30, 2016, the Federal Court of Appeal in Canada ruled that the government had failed to adequaltely consult with indigenous people over the proposed $7.9 billion Enbridge Northern Gateway pipeline, which would have used a dangerous route through ancestral indigenous territory to bring Tar Sands oil to an international port.

properties.Name: Kinder Morgan - TransMountain
properties.Image: On May 18, 2016, the Canadian National Energy Board recommended approval of the 890,000 barrel-per-day expansion project, bringing the struggle against this Kinder Morgan pipeline straight to the top. The Trudeau government will now have to show what it's made of.

properties.Name: TransCanada - Energy East
properties.Image: It would repurpose an antiquated natural gas pipeline to bring 1.1 million barrels of oil a day from Alberta and Saskatchewan through Quebec and on to New Brunswick for export. In June of 2016 the Canadian National Energy Board started a 21-month environmental review process, leaving a good chance of stopping this huge and useless project.

properties.Name: Stop the Portland - Montreal Pipeline
properties.website:
Route: Portland, Maine - North Troy, VT/High Water, QC - Montreal, QC
Capacity: 600,000 bpd
properties.EPA: The reversal of these two pipelines, built to carry imported crude from Portland to Montreal, would provide a significant foreign market for Tar Sands dilbit, which reaches Montreal via Enbridge Line 9. The reversal is currently blocked by a 2014 city ordinance banning the export of crude oil. The Portland Pipe Line Corporation is fighting the city of South Portland in court over the ordinance, which is a crucial piece in the effective blockade of the failing but still deadly dangerous Tar Sands project.

properties.Name: Bayou Bridge pipeline
properties.Image: This 24-inch pipeline, proposed and funded by Energy Transfer Partners, Philips 66 and Sunoco Logistics, would be the last leg of the DAPL, bringing Bakken crude from Texas to refineries in Louisiana. It would pass directly beneath the Atchafalaya Basin - the largest remaining wetlands in the United States.
